# create a function to convert character date time to Datetime format and extract year
 lev <- c()
 extract.year <- function(x) {
   dates <- as.POSIXct(x, format = "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
   year = format(dates,format = "%Y")
   level = levels(as.factor(year))
   num = sum(year != "2017")
   for (i in 1:length(level)) {
     if (level[i] != "2017") {
       lev[i] <- level[i]
       lev <- na.omit(lev)
     } 
   }
   return(paste0("there are ", num, " not in year 2017", " and with extra levels of ", paste(unlist(lev), collapse=', ')))
 }
extract.year(tripdata_df$lpep_pickup_datetime)
## [1] "there are 140 not in year 2017 and with extra levels of 2009, 2010, 2018"
## contain years other than 2017 in this dataset

Q3

# extract date function where only 2017-12 associated events in the dataset were extracted.
extract.dec.date <- function(x) {
   date.time <- as.POSIXct(x, format = "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
   date = as_date(date.time)
   dec.date <- update(date, year = 2017, month = 12)
   return(dec.date)
}
dec.date <- extract.dec.date(tripdata_df$lpep_pickup_datetime)

# add a new column with date only and filter inly 2017-12 by passing logical values then plot bar graph showing frequency by day
tripdata_df %>%   
  mutate(pickup_date = as_date(lpep_pickup_datetime)) %>%
  select(pickup_date) %>%
  filter(pickup_date == dec.date) %>%
  ggplot(aes(pickup_date)) + geom_bar() +
  labs(title = "Pickup Frequency",x = "Date", y = "Count") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

Q4

# method 1
## using hour() from lubridate package to extract hour component after format timedate to timestamp
HourOfDay <- function(x) {
   date.time <- as.POSIXct(x, format = "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
   hour = hour(date.time)
   return(hour)
 }

# method 2
## using format() to extract hour
HourOfDay <- function(x) {
   hour = format(as.POSIXct(x,format="%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),"%H")
   return(hour)
 }

# method 3
## using strptime() and then hour()
HourOfDay <- function(x) {
  hour = strptime(x, format = "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S") 
return(hour(x))
}

# covert datetime format to extract date only
extract.date <- function(x) {
   date.time <- as.POSIXct(x, format = "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
   date = as_date(date.time)
   return(date)
 }
date <- extract.date(tripdata_df$lpep_pickup_datetime)
# add date column to dataset
tripdata_df$date <- date
#group by date select trip distance
trip.date.df <- tripdata_df %>% group_by(date) %>% select(trip_distance, date)
# using aggregate function to calculate total trip distance by date
agg.df <- aggregate(trip_distance ~ date, trip.date.df, sum) 
# filter out invalid date which is not in 2017
agg.df.2017.12 <- agg.df[format(agg.df$date, format = "%Y-%m") == "2017-12", ]
# sort trip diatance in a decreasing manner
agg.df.2017.12.ordered  <- agg.df.2017.12[order(agg.df.2017.12$trip_distance), ]
ggplot(agg.df.2017.12.ordered, aes(x=date, y=trip_distance)) + 
  geom_col()

# identified least trips on 2017-12-25 which makes sense that most people were with family celebrating Christmas
